&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bistrot&lt;/em&gt; is the little brother of the world-famous restaurant in the Italian resort of &lt;em&gt;Forte dei Marmi, &lt;/em&gt;where the concept and atmosphere of the legendary place were brought to Moscow. Designers have recreated the interiors of a Tuscan mansion with a terrace, rounded window openings and a fountain in the patio. The feeling of an ancient family house is underlined by the open fire, oak cabinets and sideboards, lamps with shades, wicker chairs and pictures on the walls.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The gastronomic feature of Bistrot&amp;#8217;s menu is certainly traditional Tuscan cuisine, but also traditional pasta and pizza were not left without attention. Also, the chef Maxim Hazov recommends guests to pay attention to the rich selection of seafood.&lt;/p&gt;
